    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nThe table returned by `vim.system():wait()` only contains `{ code, signal, stdout, stderr }`.\nCallers that need to log or display the invoked command must store or duplicate the argument list themselves (e.g. repeating `{ 'rg', '-V' }` in health checks).\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nExtend the return table with a `cmd` field holding the exact command definition that was executed:\n```lua\nlocal job = vim.system({ 'rg', '-V' }):wait()\n-- job.cmd  → { 'rg', '-V' }\n```\n_See the original suggestion [here](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/34702#discussion_r2173778460)_",
    "closed_at": "2025-06-30T12:35:42Z",
